Amazon Seller's Growth Diary
Date: March 27, 2026
Topic: Breaking through the "New Product Traffic Deadlock"

Today was a turning point for my Amazon business. I’ve been struggling with my new product launch—it felt like my listing was invisible. My mentor helped me realize that my Long-tail Keywords were stuck in the "Product Pages" (the bottom of competitor listings) instead of the Top of Search.

I learned that even though the suggested bid was only $0.70, just hitting that number isn't enough to "break the ice." I need to be more aggressive to win the best spots.

Key Actions Taken Today:

Diagnosed the placement: I realized my traffic was low-quality "bottom-tier" traffic.

Adjusted Bidding Strategy: I set my base bid to $0.75 and applied a 100% multiplier for "Top of Search."

The Strategy: My goal is to force Amazon's A9 algorithm to show my product at the very top of the first page for my most relevant long-tail keywords.

Next Step:
Tomorrow, I need to check the data. If the impressions go up but I still don't have sales, I have to look at my Listing Conversion (CVR). It's time to be honest about my main image and price competitiveness.

Onward and upward!
